728257f-a.text:
Yellowstone Boulevard, at the north side of this intersection with Queens Boulevard, showing the Boerum farmhouse. This building may still stand in a remodeled form (stucco). It was formerly on the south side of the intersection of White Pot Road (gone in 1927) and Hoffman Boulevard (not part of Queens Boulevard.) John E. Backhus was
the owner in 1909.
March 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
728257f-a.folder: Yellowstone Boulevard & Queens Boulevard, Queens, NY

727730f-b.text:
Queens Boulevard (trolley tracks thereon), east from Yellowstone Boulevard (formerly White Pot Road left foreground), showing an old house remodelled and stuccoed in 1923. This is a set of three views. Views No. 1 shows the rear of the house, No. two shows the front of it, and No. three a partial view.
February 1923.
Views 2&3: May 1926.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

727728f-b.text:
Queens Boulevard (trolley tracks thereon), east from Yellowstone Boulevard (formerly White Pot Road; left foreground), showing an old house remodeled and stuccoed in 1923. This is a set of two views. This house was occupied for years by Charles Reitenbach, a blacksmith, later by the Forrest Park Riding School.
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
